bgm.name: ダンジョン ・やや緊張感

parameters: Roselitte frowned while looking through her belongings.

\n<Roselitte>"Yes... It's a ring given to me by Lord Yuri. I had it
stored in my luggage, but..."

\n<Ameria>"Hmm... If it's valuable, maybe it got stolen... What should
we do? Should we look for it?"

\n<Roselitte>"No, our first priority should be to escape from here. I'm
sure Lord Yuri would understand."
\n<Ameria>"Understood. Then, let's work together and do our best!"

\n<Ameria>"...But, while we need to hurry and get out of here, we
shouldn't neglect our preparations. Don't forget to 'record
in the journal' either."
\n<Roselitte>"Of course. Then, let's make a record right away--"

Roselitte reached for her luggage again but froze with a
frown on her face.

\n<Ameria>"Hmm... then here, Roselitte-san. Feel free to use my
journal."
Ameria handed her journal to Roselitte.

You can now save the game. ※Press the S key (default) for a
shortcut call.

\n<Roselitte>"...It was your treasure, wasn't it? Are you sure I can use
it?"

\n<Ameria>"Don't worry about it! Given the situation, it's fine to
think of it as your own."
\n<Roselitte>"...Thank you. Then, if you'll excuse me..."

\n<Roselitte>"...No. As I said before, writing in the journal doesn't
seem to lift my spirits."

\n<Ameria>"Ahaha. But don't worry. I'll take a look at Roselitte-san's
injuries and cheer you up."
Ameria said with a beaming smile.

\n<Ameria>"Thinking that I'm useful to Roselitte-san makes me happy,
and I feel like it gives me energy!"

\n<Ameria>"Anyway, don't forget to 'record frequently.' It's bound to
be useful later on."
\n<Ameria>"...Oh, right. I almost forgot another important thing."

\n<Ameria>"That head injury... I'm sure you're well aware, but using
great power means you also risk hurting yourself. So please,
try not to overdo it."

\n<Ameria>"But I think there will be times in the battles ahead when
you absolutely must use your power. So for those times, make
sure to receive my treatment regularly."
\n<Roselitte>"You don't have to go to such lengths..."
Ameria peered into Roselitte's face as if scrutinizing her.
